Introduction

Choi Yeonjun is a South Korean singer-songwriter, rapper, dancer, and composer under Big Hit Entertainment and HYBE Labels. He is best known as the oldest member of the boy group TXT.

Yeonjun made headlines when he was unveiled as the first member of Big Hit's newest boy group, TXT (Tomorrow X Together). Yeonjun trained for four years and was said to be a former trainee under Cube Entertainment. While training, he performed as a backup dancer on several stages.

On March 4, 2019, Yeonjun officially debuted as a member of TXT through the first mini-album ‘The Dream Chapter: STAR’.

On September 19, 2024, Yeonjun made his solo debut with the single album "GGUM".
